<chapter condition="TITLE=Services: Payee Maintenance;PERM=sy_payee_register_billp_access;ACCESS=SY_CUS_PAY"
	role="TOPIC">
  <title>Payee Maintenance</title>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Overview</title>

    <para role="TEXT">As an administrator at a client company, you use the
    <application>Payee Maintenance</application> module to register and
    maintain Bill payment and Direct debit Authorisations.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">These payments have been loaded into the <xi:include
    href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_appli"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/> through other modules and
    facilities.</para>
 </section>
    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Payee Maintenance Options</title>

      <para role="TEXT">The Payee Maintenance options are part of the System
      Features menu. They are as follows:</para>

      <variablelist role="TEXT">
        <varlistentry>
          <term><guisubmenu>Register - Bill Payment</guisubmenu></term>

          <listitem>
            <para role="TEXT">Register Bills loaded into the system</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term><guisubmenu>Update - Bill Payment</guisubmenu></term>

          <listitem>
            <para role="TEXT">Update previous Bills registered into the system</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
    </section>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Payee Maintenance - Register Bill Payment</title>

      <para role="TEXT">Register Bills loaded into the system.</para>

      <para role="TEXT">When you select this option, you are presented with a
      list of all the existing bills in the system. You can search the list by
      entering search criteria in the <guilabel moreinfo="none">Bank,
      </guilabel><guilabel moreinfo="none">Payee Name, </guilabel><guilabel
      moreinfo="none">Category, </guilabel><guilabel
      moreinfo="none">Status</guilabel> and <guilabel>Actor</guilabel> fields
      at the top of the page.</para>

      <note>
        <para role="TEXT">The <guilabel>Status</guilabel> and <guilabel>Actor</guilabel>
        fields are available if maker-checker functionality is enabled.</para>
      </note>

      <para role="TEXT">The list of existing customer counterparties has the
      following columns:</para>

      <informaltable role="TEXT">
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="2.0*"/>

          <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="8.0*"/>

          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Field</para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Description</para></entry>
            </row>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry><guilabel moreinfo="none"> Bank</guilabel></entry>

              <entry>The Payee's Bank</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Payee
              Name</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">The name of the Payee</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel
              moreinfo="none">Category</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">The category of the
              bill</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Payee
              Description</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">The description of the
              Payee.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry
              valign="top"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel>Status</guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">This indicates the status of the
              pending record set by the checker. </para><note>
                  <para role="TEXT">This column is only available if maker-checker
                  functionality is enabled.</para>
                </note></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel>Maker User
              </guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Displays the user ID of the maker of
              the transaction.</para><note>
                  <para role="TEXT">This column is only available if maker-checker
                  functionality is enabled.</para>
                </note></entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </informaltable>

      <para role="TEXT">Click the <guibutton moreinfo="none">Register Bill
      Payment</guibutton> button at the bottom of the list to register a bill
      payment payee. When you select this option, you are presented with a
      list of all the Bill Payees that has been configured for your user
      profile. You can search the list by entering search criteria in the
      <guilabel moreinfo="none">Bank, </guilabel><guilabel
      moreinfo="none">Payee Name,</guilabel><guilabel moreinfo="none">
      Category</guilabel> and <guilabel>Payee Description</guilabel> fields at
      the top of the page. Click on the required row to view the General
      Details form for the Bill Payee. The form is as follows:</para>

      <section role="ITEM">
        <title>Register Bill Payment form - General Details</title>

        <para role="TEXT">When a bill entry is selected the Register Payee -
        Bill Payment form is displayed. This form allows the Entity to be
        allocated to the bill for payment.<informaltable role="TEXT">
            <tgroup cols="3">
              <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="2.0*"/>

              <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="1.0*"/>

              <colspec colname="c3" colwidth="6.0*"/>

              <thead>
                <row>
                  <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Field</para></entry>

                  <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Type</para></entry>

                  <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Description</para></entry>
                </row>
              </thead>

              <tbody>
                <row>
                  <entry><guilabel moreinfo="none">Activate
                  </guilabel></entry>

                  <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                      <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/char_check.gif"
                                   role="CHAR_CHECK" width="3mm"/>
                      </imageobject>
                    </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                  <entry>This box is ticked to indicate the Bill will be
                  registered. (Click the Cancel button at the bottom of the
                  screen to cancel the registration)</entry>
                </row>

                <row>
                  <entry><guilabel moreinfo="none">Entity </guilabel></entry>

                  <entry valign="top"><inlinemediaobject>
                      <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/char_excla.gif"
                                   role="CHAR_EXCLA" width="2mm"/>
                      </imageobject>
                    </inlinemediaobject><inlinemediaobject>
                      <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/char_action.gif"
                                   role="CHAR_ACTION" width="3mm"/>
                      </imageobject>
                    </inlinemediaobject></entry>

                  <entry>Entity within your company that this Bill is to be
                  allocated to. Click the magnifying glass icon to display and
                  select from a list of valid Entities.</entry>
                </row>

                <row>
                  <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Payee
                  Name</guilabel> </para></entry>

                  <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                      <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/char_excla.gif"
                                   role="CHAR_EXCLA" width="2mm"/>
                      </imageobject>
                    </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                  <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">The name of the Payee.
                  </para></entry>
                </row>

                <row>
                  <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel
                  moreinfo="none">Description</guilabel> </para></entry>

                  <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                      <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/char_excla.gif"
                                   role="CHAR_EXCLA" width="2mm"/>
                      </imageobject>
                    </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                  <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">The description of the bill. This
                  field can be updated at this stage if
                  required.</para></entry>
                </row>

                <row>
                  <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel moreinfo="none">Bill
                  Ref </guilabel> </para></entry>

                  <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                      <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/char_excla.gif"
                                   role="CHAR_EXCLA" width="2mm"/>
                      </imageobject>
                    </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                  <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">The reference for the bill payee.
                  </para><note>
                      <para role="TEXT">This can be a text field or a dropdown based on
                      the settings selected by the Bank administrator.</para>
                    </note></entry>
                </row>
              </tbody>
            </tgroup>
          </informaltable></para>

        <para role="TEXT">After allocating the Entity and updating the
        description, click the <emphasis role="bold">Save</emphasis> button at
        the bottom of the screen to save the updated payee. Click
        <guibutton>Submit</guibutton> to submit the details.</para>
      </section>
    </section>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Payee Maintenance - Update Bill Payment</title>

      <para role="TEXT">Update Registered Payees. The option provides the
      facility to change the Entity or description of a registered Bill
      Payee.</para>

      <para role="TEXT">When you select this option, you are presented with a
      list of all the outstanding registered Bill Payees in the system. You
      can search the list by entering search criteria in the <guilabel
      moreinfo="none">Bank, </guilabel><guilabel moreinfo="none">Payee
      Name</guilabel> and <guilabel moreinfo="none">Category</guilabel> fields
      at the top of the page.</para>

